reviews.text: nice food, MIT will save a lot if you have the membership.
Food quality is very good service is great

My first ever visit to The Spaghetti House, and I must say I’m impressed!

We went on the last public holiday of the Chinese New Year, as expected, there will be some wait, but wasn’t too long, we got our table in less than half an hour.

The food arrive quite quickly after we have ordered, and they were all very hot and tasty, and the portions are quite big too! I really liked the lobster bisque and the lobster risotto. 

The staffs were amazingly friendly and helpful, and very attentive though it was a busy night. They have a semi open kitchen concept, so we can see the staffs preparing the food, and they all seem very efficient and the space is very clean.

Would definitely come back, especially now I have joined their VIP program.
Great food and service.
Nice environment. Good food and price. The afternoon tea must try.
